Accommodations may include but are not limited to: conducting interviews in accessible locations that accommodate mobility needs, encouraging candidates to bring and use any existing assistive technology such as screen readers and offering flexible interview formats such as virtual or phone interviews.

Create Your Better Tomorrow


With over 50 years of experience in the industry, Kollmorgen, a Regal Rexnord brand, is a technology leader in navigation and fleet control of automated guided vehicles (AGVs) and autonomous mobile robots (AMRs). As part of our continue effort to innovate and grow, we are now expanding and are seeking talents to join us and part of our success story.

Our definition of success goes beyond customer satisfaction; it includes fostering the talent of tomorrow. At Kollmorgen, we cultivate a collaborative and inclusive environment where innovation thrives and every individual is valued. Our commitment to professional growth and development ensures that you will have the opportunity to advance your career while working on cutting-edge automation solutions.

We are looking for a Quality Assurance (QA) Leader, a system test- and integration leader, to be part of a dynamic team that is passionate about making a difference in the world of AGVs and AMRs.
Position Overview

As a QA Lead, you will be part of our Engineering department, along with other 60+ engineers working within embedded systems, system software as well as windows applications and web services. You will be part of a team that assists in building and supporting an agile development environment, including developing and maintaining the continuous delivery pipeline (CI/CD). You will also support the integration of assets, end-to-end solution testing, DevOps practices, deployment and release.

In this position, you'll ensure software quality by overseeing engineering processes and adherence to standards, collaborating on Automatic Regression Tests, hosting the Software Quality Assurance (SQA) Community of Practice (CoP), coordinating with stakeholders, leading system integration and test planning, and actively participating in testing to deliver reliable software solutions.

What does success look like in this position:
  • Effective Quality Assurance strategies and test planning: Implement QA strategies, test plans, and clarify System Release Test activities;
  • Balanced test suits and tools: Ensure test suits and tools support speed and quality;
  • Thorough Documenting acceptance criteria validation: Document how acceptance criteria are validated (ISO 27001);
  • Robust Quality Assurance of the NDC system: Ensure quality assurance of the system of our solution (NDC) and communicate status;
  • Effective hosting CoP for Quality Assurance: Host the CoP for Quality Assurance and make decisions;
  • Collaborative work with development teams: Work with development teams to schedule testing;
  • Continuous improvement of loop times: Review and improve loop times for developers and stakeholders;
  • Progressive evolution of the CI/CD pipeline: Evolve the CI/CD pipeline to shorten lead times.
Tech Stack

Jest, Git, Azure DevOps, SonarQube, BrowserStack, C#, Python, Robot Framework, Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD, MongoDB, SikuliX, VMware, E2E tests; Playwright and Selenium.

While experience with all these technologies is beneficial, it is not a strict requirement. We value a willingness to learn and adapt, and we provide ample support for skill development.

To achieve the mission and success of this position, we believe you already have:
  • Educational background in Computer science, IT, Engineering, or equivalent;
  • At least 6 years of experience within Software- and System quality assurance;
  • Solid knowledge in Testing methodologies and building CI/CD pipelines;
  • Technical proficiency in various testing techniques and industry-standard quality assurance methodologies;
  • Experience from leadership roles and from Leading System testing;
  • Fluency in English, both spoken and written;
  • Strong collaboration and communication skills;
  • Ability to anticipate, address, and solve complex problems;
  • Commitment to high standards and continuous quality improvement;
  • Drive to challenge the status quo to create breakthrough innovations;
  • Flexibility and adaptability in changing circumstances.

It is beneficial that if you also have prior working experience within AGV & AMR domain.

We see that our ideal candidates are committed to personal & professional growth, and they share our core values and genuine enthusiasm for innovation.


Additional Information

Full time employment | Based in Mölndal, Sweden

Selection takes place on an ongoing basis, so be sure to apply early. We're excited to hear from you!

Kollmorgen - Autonomous Mobile Solutions

We offer a complete automation solution for AGV and AMR providers. Our NDC Solutions platform is a proven platform that enables efficient and reliable vehicle automation with increased performance. It includes all hardware, software, and navigation technologies necessary to automate a vehicle fleet. The platform has been installed in a vast variety of material handling sites and vehicles across the globe.

description:
Goeteborg, Sweden

Relocation friendly

Software - Other

Automotive Industry

20/12/2024

Req. VR-110280
Project description

Revolutionizing the Automotive Industry with the Fastest Software Factory

Customers Software-in-the-Loop (SIL) initiative is transforming how they develop and validate software at scale. The goals:

- Ensure consistently reliable software products.
- Accelerate integration testing by identifying issues early—without reliance on physical hardware.
- Minimize testing and deployment times through fast, scalable virtual testing.
- Enable rapid evaluations and accelerated progress in early project phases.

By automating and streamlining testing, customer empowers developers with immediate feedback while delivering exceptional vehicles to their customers.

Responsibilities

You will:

Lead the technical development of Software-in-the-Loop tools and methods, ensuring scalability, performance, and reliability

Work hands-on to design, code, and deliver robust solutions that developers trust.

Innovate and improve the current SIL ecosystem, introducing cutting-edge tools and approaches to enhance functionality and usability.

Collaborate with developers, architects, and other stakeholders to identify needs and align tool development with broader R&D goals.

Optimize workflows to improve developer experience and adoption of SIL practices

Skills

Must have

Proven expertise in developing and improving Software-in-the-Loop solutions for testing and validation in complex systems.

Advanced programming skills in Python, C++, or similar languages.

Strong experience with software development best practices, including design, implementation, and testing.

Nice to have

Expertise in cloud infrastructure (e.g., AWS).

Proficiency with CI/CD pipelines (e.g., Zuul, Jenkins).

Familiarity with SIL and simulation standards.

Experience with SIL and Virtual ECU tools used in the automotive industry (e.g., Silver, emulators).

Knowledge of HIL tools (e.g., dSPACE, Vector).

Proficiency in Linux and POSIX environments.

Understanding of automotive operating systems, standards, and protocols (e.g., QNX, AUTOSAR, CAN, LIN, Flexray, Ethernet, SOME/IP).

Experience with CAE, simulations, and modeling.

Other

Languages

English: C1 Advanced

Seniority

Senior

Goeteborg, Sweden

C/C++

Automotive Industry

24/12/2024

Req. VR-110518
Project description

The scope of this project is to strengthen the automotive project with Functional Safety Engineer and SW development, responsible for the development and enabling of a Converged Infotainment platform solution based on Android Automotive and QNX with a Hypervisor solution. The supplier delivers FuSa Engineer and Senior SW development resources.

Responsibilities

During the project, Luxoft shall: provide experts to work on deliverables with the sufficient qualifications and skills to perform activities as mentioned herein.

Luxoft shall work according to Automotive project defined working processes using customer SW development practice and SW repositories, build systems and CI Chain.

Luxoft experts shall follow the defined and agreed time plan.

Luxoft is responsible for people management setup. The people management setup will be focused on mood monitoring and staff risks assessment.

Skills

Must have

-B.S. or M.S. in Electrical or Computer Engineering with an emphasis on software development for embedded systems

-Extensive knowledge of C++ programming, with a solid understanding of ASPICE or ISO 26262 standards.

-Over 5 years of experience developing automated tests for embedded systems, specifically in the automotive infotainment sector.

-Skilled in building comprehensive unit and system tests to verify the functionality of software implementations.

-Proficiency in using Python for automation and integration testing

-Proficient in using Linux commands and Docker for development and deployment.

Fluent in English, with the capability to produce clear and concise technical software documentation.

Familiarity with Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA) and risk mode analysis for requirements.

Nice to have

Experience with QNX Real-Time OS: Proficient in developing applications on the QNX real-time operating system, with a strong understanding of its architecture and use cases in embedded systems.

Functional Safety (FuSA) Engineering: Experience in functional safety engineering, particularly within the context of automotive systems, ensuring compliance with safety standards and protocols.

In Car Testing: Hands-on experience in conducting Car testing, including performance, reliability, and compliance testing for automotive systems.

Other

Languages

English: C1 Advanced

Seniority

Senior

description:
We are now looking for Employeneurs to join the Production Development team in Gothenburg. As an Embedded Developer in Automotive, you will be an important part of the Automotive solutions in the future.
YOUR CHALLENGES?
You will be a part of a team that develop the future vehicle systems. In this role you need to be structured, social, trustworthy & driven. Working as an embedded software developer, means being a professional who specializes in designing, developing, and maintaining software applications that are specifically designed to run on embedded systems.
WHAT DO WE EXPECT FROM YOU?
B.Sc./M.Sc. degree in Electrical, Electronics, Mechatronics, Data science, Software or other relevant academic background. Minimum 2 years of experience in relevant filed.
Experience within any below is desirable:
Experience in embedded software development
Experience working with GIT, Jenkins, Jira, System Weaver, AUTOSAR or MATLAB(Simulink).
Experience and knowledge of C, C++, Java, Python or Figma.

WHY CHOOSE EMPLOYENEURSHIP?
We are truly unique thanks to our Employeneurship model which is a true innovation for the High Technology consulting business. It is the business relationship of the 21st century for high skilled technical professionals. It is built around 5 main pillars:
You will have a permanent employment contract, offering you stability and security
You will get to know your market value and have a share in the profit your work generates thanks to the individual profit sharing
We will support you with a one-on-one coaching and trainings designed to help you develop your entrepreneurial skills
The competence cells structure, provides you with a strong meaningful and relevant network
The entrepreneurial lab: a playground for new ideas and a potential launching for start-ups

B.Sc./M.Sc. degree in Electrical, Electronics, Mechatronics, Data science, Software or other relevant academic background. Minimum 2 years of experience in relevant filed.

Experience within any below is desirable:
Experience in embedded software development
Experience working with GIT, Jenkins, Jira, System Weaver, AUTOSAR or MATLAB(Simulink).
Experience and knowledge of C, C++, Java, Python or Figma.

WHY CHOOSE EMPLOYENEURSHIP?
We are truly unique thanks to our Employeneurship model which is a true innovation for the High Technology consulting business. It is the business relationship of the 21st century for high skilled technical professionals. It is built around 5 main pillars:
You will have a permanent employment contract, offering you stability and security
You will get to know your market value and have a share in the profit your work generates thanks to the individual profit sharing
We will support you with a one-on-one coaching and trainings designed to help you develop your entrepreneurial skills
The competence cells structure, provides you with a strong meaningful and relevant network
The entrepreneurial lab: a playground for new ideas and a potential launching for start-ups

description:
Help us shape the future of mobility

At Volvo Cars, we’re on an exciting journey to shape the future of mobility. We’re building direct relationships with customers, and aim to be a leader in new technology. It’s so exciting – we’re well on our way on our journey towards full electrification. Join us and become a part of our vision for the future – a future that's both exciting and a catalyst for positive change.

Let's introduce ourselves

By joining our team as a Senior Test Automation Engineer, you will become part of a dynamic and innovative company that thrives on excellence and continuous improvement. We offer a stimulating work environment that encourages personal and professional growth, supported by opportunities for ongoing learning and development.

As part of our team, you will have the chance to work on exciting projects that push the boundaries of automotive technology, collaborating with talented professionals from diverse backgrounds. We value a culture of teamwork, respect, and inclusion, ensuring that every team member's voice is heard, and contributions are recognized.

The Complete HIL department performs system- and integration-testing for distributed vehicle and user functions, system performance testing and ADAS scenario testing on complete system level. The test environment consists of the electrical system of the vehicle, including all relevant ECUs, and actuators as well as environment and traffic simulations and sensor data emulations.

Testing is performed both manually and automated, where the automated regression is an essential part of delivering test results fast to the developing organization.

What you'll do

As a senior automation engineer you work in a team of engineers to build and maintain the automation framework, handling build and execution as well as publishing and visualization of test results. You work closely with the test developers to support the needs, making sure that the automation is always functional and up and running.
As a senior automation engineer you also work in the bigger organization to make sure the automation is compatible with the overall CI- and reporting structure of Volvo Cars.

What you'll bring

As a person we believe you are driven and well organized, with the ability to work independently with the tasks at hand. It is also important that you can share your knowledge, and collaborate well both inside the team, and with other teams in the group and organization.

Fundamental requirements include excellent Python programming knowledge, Jenkins, Git (Gerrit), Robot Framework or similar, Jira, and knowledge of Agile/SAFe methodologies.

Meritorious skills include PowerBI, Grafana, dSpace, ISTQB certification, and knowledge of Matlab/Simulink. Volvo Product Development skills are also meritorious.

Ready to Take the Next Step?

Please submit your application through our career page. Due to GDPR regulations, we’re unable to store or consider applications from other platforms. Make sure to submit your application in English.

Once your application is successfully submitted, you’ll receive a confirmation email. Applications are open until 6th of January 2025. We’re excited to get to know you!

Volvo Cars – driving change together

Volvo Cars’ success is the result of a collaborative, diverse and inclusive working environment. Today, we’re one of the most well-known and respected car brands, with around 43,000 employees across the globe. At Volvo Cars, your career is designed around your skills and aspirations, so you can reach your fullest potential.

And it’s so exciting – we’re well on our way on our journey towards full electrification. We have five fully electric cars already on the market, and five more on the way. Our fully-electric and plug-in hybrid cars combined make up almost 50 per cent of our sales. So come and join us in shaping the future of mobility. There’s never been a more rewarding time to play your part in our inspiring and creative teams!

Curious about Life at Volvo Cars? Read more

Curious about our story? Read more

description:
Goeteborg, Sweden

Automated Testing Python

Automotive Industry

20/12/2024

Req. VR-110277
Project description

Participate in the process of test system flow by defining test activities, equipment, asset under test and DUT (Device Under Test) preparedness together with requirement owner and suppliers.

Responsibilities

Be responsible for the VCU component verification, i.e. black and white box test, acceptance test and regression test on deliverables from supplier (both inhouse and external)

Automate test cases in vTestStudio for Component-/Domain

and Complete testing in bench rig, HIL and on Vehicle. Test Cases to automate are from all functional areas within Door, Alarm and Tailgate not just VCU.

Create and maintain automation test framework in Python and C++ (EMON).

Test methods & test case development in Carweaver, planning and coordination of test activities together with rest of the team.

Create Fault reports and assign to receiver in such way that an investigation and solution can be provided under function or system owners leadership. Review and communicate with suppliers' test reports and results.

Independently take logs and measurement on the component and actuators and signals.

In collaboration with developer analyze logs to identify faults.

Ensure the work is delivered as per specified acceptance criteria and definition.

Read out and analyze nightly runs in our HILs

Skills

Must have

Programming knowledge in Python and C++

Knowledge and understanding how to read electrical schematics, use of instruments such as voltmeters and oscilloscopes

Experience from automotive industry

Experiences of the following tools is preferred: Elektra, Canalyzer/Canoe, Inca, DSA, Car config edit, Carcom, Team Center

Proven experience from manual and automated verification of embedded software, using tools like vector hardware & software

Swedish B-driver license

Master of Science within software, electronics, mechatronics or similar

Personal qualities

Passion for new technologies, software and hardware test and creating great user experiences.

Willing to take up the task that is most important for the team to progress.

A positive and easy-going mindset.

Strong self-driven ability.

Curious and communicative, the ability to write and verbally explain complex issues

Fluent in English

Nice to have

Passion for new technologies, software and hardware test and creating great user experiences.

Willing to take up the task that is most important for the team to progress.

A positive and easy-going mindset.

Strong self-driven ability.

Curious and communicative, the ability to write and verbally explain complex issues

Swedish is a merit

Other

Languages

English: C1 Advanced

Seniority

Regular

description:
At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.

Jeppesen, a subsidiary of The Boeing Company, is one of the largest software development companies in Gothenburg. We develop and implement innovative resource management and optimization solutions for the world’s leading airlines. We are dedicated to continuous improvement and delivering more value to our clients.

At Jeppesen’s office in central Gothenburg you will work in a one-of-a-kind software development organization with solutions that make a real difference to people around the world. You will be working in an agile learning organization, surrounded by a team of talented, creative and dedicated colleagues. You will learn and broaden your perspective by working with 400 professionals from more than 50 different nations, but also be part of a global organization allowing for collaboration with customers and colleagues across the world. Most importantly, you will be expected to make a difference.

Jeppesen is looking for a Senior Cloud Developer for our Software Engineering & Advance Technology department based in Gothenburg, Sweden.

About the position:
Are you a talented software developer with a passion for cloud architecture and experience building cloud native applications? We have an exciting opportunity for you at our office in Gothenburg, Sweden.

You'll fit right in if you're a natural team player with strong communication skills and a fast learner who is passionate about sharing knowledge and empowering your colleagues. You are not afraid to bring your creative solutions up for discussion backed by your real-world experience with cloud-native apps.

Join our small, cross-functional team that is leading the charge in transforming our organization's processes to be cloud-native. We're on a mission to redesign, simplify, accelerate, and ensure reliable deployments to our cloud environments worldwide.

As a Cloud Developer, you will collaborate with various teams including Software Development, Support, Sales and Customer Solutions, to define our cutting-edge SaaS product. Your responsibilities will include developing services supporting our Planning solution, evolving the deployment infrastructure and security, building tools and applications to enhance customer interaction, and supporting the transition to a cloud-based infrastructure.

Required Qualifications:

- Strong experience in backend development and microservices architecture

- Working knowledge of cloud platforms, particularly AWS

- Understanding of containerization and Kubernetes

- A degree in Computer Science or equivalent job experience

Preferred Qualifications:

- Strong development experience in one or more languages (Python, Go, Java etc)

- Experience with architectural design of cloud-native services

- Knowledge of observability practices and tools (metrics, logging, tracing)

- Familiarity with containerization technologies

- Experience with Unix/Linux environments

At our company, we embrace continuous integration, delivery, and deployment methodologies. Our tech stack is built for modern cloud-native development. We embrace DevOps culture with continuous integration, delivery, and deployment methodologies at our core. You'll work with an exciting array of cutting-edge technologies including GitOps, AWS services, Kubernetes, OpenTelemetry, and more.

Relocation:
This position does not offer relocation. Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense.

This position is hybrid. This means that the selected candidate will be required to perform some work onsite 2-3 days a week. This is at the hiring team’s discretion and could potentially change in the future.

Visa Sponsorship:
Employer will initiate the visa application; however, the successful candidate will cover the cost of visa.

Join our team of passionate developers who are shaping the future of our SaaS solution. We offer a collaborative work environment, professional growth opportunities, and competitive compensation. Don't miss out on this chance to be part of the next big thing in the Airline business!

Please apply by sending your CV in English.

Export Control Requirements: Not an export control position

Equal Opportunity Employer:

We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not accept unlawful discrimination in our recruitment or employment practices on any grounds including but not limited to; race, color, ethnicity, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, physical or mental disability, genetic factors, military and veteran status, or other characteristics covered by applicable law.

We have teams in more than 65 countries, and each person plays a role in helping us become one of the world’s most innovative, diverse and inclusive companies. We are proud members of the Valuable 500 and welcome applications from candidates with disabilities. Applicants are encouraged to share with our recruitment team any accommodations required during the recruitment process. Accommodations may include but are not limited to: conducting interviews in accessible locations that accommodate mobility needs, encouraging candidates to bring and use any existing assistive technology such as screen readers and offering flexible interview formats such as virtual or phone interviews.

description:
We are looking for a SW Development Engineer- Simulink/TargetLink for a global automotive company in Gothenburg.

The company design and monitor different temperature levels, cooling down, heating up, transfer/transport and store heat for electric motors, batteries, control modules etc. All with sustainability in focus. Together they have complete ownership of Thermal Management systems from first architectural sketch to software release & monitoring in vehicles. Your focus will be SW development for controlling the Thermal System.

The company promises you 14 diverse colleagues with high ambitions, they are characterized as an open and friendly team, where everyone shares their knowledge with each other.

The company sees that you have at least a BSc within mechatronic, electrical or electronics and solid experience within SW development. You have previous experience from SW development and CI toolchains is a natural part of your working process.

Required Skills:

Experience from SW development, at least 6 years.
Simulink, Target link experience is a prerequisite
Understanding of Continuous Integration tools such as GIT and Gerrit
Curious, structured, good analytical skills and a great technical interest
System design and Function development within automotive development is beneficial.
Experience from Thermal Management system is meritorious
C/C++ and Python experience is highly meritorious
Driving licence (B) is a definitive prerequisite
Driving licence (BE) is meritorious

Last, but not least, you are a supportive team player that believes in inclusiveness and contribute with personal energy!

This is a full-time consultant position through Incluso in Gothenburg. Start is in January, One year's limited contract to begin with, possibility of extension after that.

Please submit your CV as soon as possible since we will review the applications on an on-going basis.

For more information about this role, please contact Kanika Singhal, recruiter at Incluso.

description:
Goeteborg, Sweden

Android

Automotive Industry

20/12/2024

Req. VR-110301
Project description

Support the customer’s objective to make all cars connected and provide a continuously enhanced experience for both new and existing cars.
You will be developing the next generation infotainment system based on Google's Android automotive OS.
The work is done in an Agile team with a warm atmosphere, a speak up culture and a place where everyone can be themselves. Collaboration is highly valued, and the team effort always comes before the individual.

You are proactive, adaptable, and always looking for ways to improve processes and outcomes. Above all, you are a team player who values integrity, innovation, and excellence.

Responsibilities

As an Android Application Developer, you will:

Develop software for the infotainment system.

Collaborate with partners like Google, UX designers, and other development teams to define a coherent end-to-end solution.

Participate in the entire software development lifecycle, including:

Design

Architecture

Documentation

Development

Verification

Validation

Stay up to date with the latest industry trends and best practices to ensure our solutions remain at the forefront of technology.

Skills

Must have

A M.Sc in Software Engineering or at least 5 years of relevant experience.

Hands-on experience in Android application development (Java/Kotlin).

Experience with AOSP and the AOSP build system.

Familiarity with modern app architectural patterns (MVP, MVVM, clean architecture).

Good knowledge of Android testing frameworks (JUnit, Espresso, Mockito).

Proficiency in Python scripting.

Expertise in version control tools such as Git.

Nice to have

Furthermore, it is meritorious if you have previous experience in Automotive infotainment projects. Also, there is a big advantage if you have a Swedish B driver's license.

Other

Languages

English: C1 Advanced

Seniority

Regular

Collaborate with partners like Google, UX designers, and other development teams to define a coherent end-to-end solution.

Participate in the entire software development lifecycle, including:

Design

Architecture

Documentation

Development

Verification

Validation

Stay up to date with the latest industry trends and best practices to ensure our solutions remain at the forefront of technology.

Skills

Must have

A M.Sc in Software Engineering or at least 5 years of relevant experience.

Hands-on experience in Android application development (Java/Kotlin).

Experience with AOSP and the AOSP build system.

Familiarity with modern app architectural patterns (MVP, MVVM, clean architecture).

Good knowledge of Android testing frameworks (JUnit, Espresso, Mockito).

Proficiency in Python scripting.

Expertise in version control tools such as Git.

Nice to have

Furthermore, it is meritorious if you have previous experience in Automotive infotainment projects. Also, there is a big advantage if you have a Swedish B driver's license.

Other

Languages

English: C1 Advanced

Seniority

Regular

description:
Benify is an international HR tech company that provides a market-leading global benefit and total rewards platform. With over 550 Benifyers in 6 countries, we're driving success with over 1500 customers and approximately three million users around the world . We empower people to be the best they can be while fostering a sustainable and engaging work culture where employees feel engaged and included "Because People Matter" .

At Benify, we have created a world-class integration platform! The capabilities of the platform includes API gateways, messaging, and a low-code integration tool! And, of course, logging and monitoring tools. In the integration platform we are using open-source products to a very large extent.

Responsibilities

As an Integration Platform Specialist, you will work with a variety of interesting and leading-edge integration components, tools, and setups within our Integration Platforms team. Your workdays will be filled with various, fast-paced, and stimulating tasks in a dynamic and diverse work environment together with motivated people. You will work with internal and external parties and support our customers with new/updated functionality and solve existing challenges in our integration landscape. You will be supporting our development teams with integration expertise, and you will have a shared responsibility for further developing and maintaining our integration landscape. In this role experience of REST API design is a must.

In your daily work, you will support agile teams and cross-functionally with other teams spread across multiple geographic locations to deliver the right data flow and flexible solutions for our clients, and you will monitor and improve our technical setup. You will work within the Integration team and work closely with the head of Integration Platforms.

Benify is practicing API First design methodology.

As Integration Platform Specialit, you will also:

Support development teams and our customer integration teams in REST APIs, messaging, and low-code development, most often as a sounding board and/or reviewer
Further develop the capabilities of our low code integration platform
Participate in overseeing operations and support our internal teams with operational information
Participate in day-to-day operations of the integration platform, including patches, admin and more
Manage CI/CD toolchains
Update info on our Developer Portal
Educate developers in our tools

Personal attributes

We are seeking someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment, takes ownership of their work, and enjoys tackling complex technical challenges. You should have a genuine passion for problem-solving, taking initiative, and being proactive, detail-oriented, and committed to continuously improving processes and tools. A collaborative mindset and strong communication skills are essential, as you will be working with diverse teams across multiple geographies.

We also see that you have

Software engineer degree, preferably BSc in computer science or equal
REST API design experience

Programming experience in JavaScript/TypeScript and Python. Experience in Java and LUA is a plus.
Professional proficiency in English, both written and spoken. Any additional languages are welcomed in our global company

It's a , thus not a requirement if you also got...

Messaging design experience (AsyncAPI)

Configuration of GitHub CI/CD tools
IdP (Identity provider) tools/systems experience

Perks of being a Benifyer

Guaranteed work-life balance with a hybrid working model
Collective agreement
Generous wellness allowance
30 days vacation
ITP1 pension
Lifeplan - a leading financial advisory service that offers personalized advice for maximizing your pension savings

Practical information

Start: As soon as we find the right match!
Extent: Full-time, 100%
Location: Stockholm or Gothenburg, Sweden.

Apply by submitting your CV and/or your LinkedIn profile using the application form below. We screen applications continuously and may hire someone before the last application date.

Please let us know if you need any reasonable adjustments for interviews by replying to the email you will receive after you apply.

As we approach the holiday season, we want to inform you that our recruitment process may take a little longer than usual due to upcoming end-of-year breaks. We kindly ask for your patience, as feedback or updates might be delayed. We will resume processing applications in January and look forward to reconnecting with you then.

Thank you for your understanding, and we wish you a restful and joyful end of the year!

description:
At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.

Jeppesen, a subsidiary of The Boeing Company, is one of the largest software development companies in Gothenburg. We develop innovative optimization solutions for the world’s leading airlines. We are dedicated to continuous improvement, delivering more value to our clients, and exploring emerging technologies such as quantum computing, AI and big data analytics.

At Jeppesen’s office in central Gothenburg you will work in a one-of-a-kind software development organization with fascinating solutions that make a real difference to people around the world. You will be working in an agile learning organization, surrounded by a team of talented, creative and dedicated colleagues. You will learn and broaden your perspective by working with 400 professionals from more than 30 different nations, but also be part of a global organization allowing for collaboration with customers and colleagues across the world. Most importantly, you will be expected to make a difference.

To find out more about our current products and solutions, please have a look at our website: https://ww2.jeppesen.com/airline-crew-optimization-solutions/

Position Responsibilities:
We are looking for a Senior Software Developer to join our team in Gothenburg. In this role, you will have a central position to develop and maintain specific software for our generic product packaging. The team is responsible to develop the Atrium Configuration Environment, which is a collection of programs and services that in a standardized way serves as the foundation for customers. The Atrium Configuration Environment is used to host, build, test and deploy the individual customer's product configuration.

Currently, the work involves porting the application to the AWS cloud. The Configuration Environment has historically existed as a collection of virtual machines, and we are currently working on replicating this setup in the cloud. We are also working on moving the services into a Kubernetes context. Most of the daily work involves writing Bash and Python scripts that manage the platform, which consists of a GitLab instance that serves the CI/CD processes and various connecting components. Each customer has their own such instance and can modify various aspects themselves. Our team create and maintain the foundation of this setup.

You will work together with a dedicated team of software engineers where collaboration and helpfulness are at the heart of our work culture. We work closely with both internal customers and other development teams as well as airline customers to develop solutions and improve user experience.

We value high product quality where our build environment, tests and CI/CD in combination with a DevSecOps mindset are crucial parts for success in our journey from on premises solutions towards Software as a Service (SaaS) solutions in a cloud environment. We strive to have strong and empowered teams that takes full responsibility and have the autonomy to be high performing, driving continuous improvement and innovation.

We believe you have a strong analytical approach to problem solving, strong communication skills both within and outside your team and an interest in technology as well as human relations. A good understanding and experience of agile methodology is highly valued. We also think you are driven, committed, have a positive attitude and are comfortable with continuous team growth and having fun. You will have great opportunities to influence, learn and grow as a software developer and individual. We offer several education and training possibilities to get under the hood of our product solutions technically and also from a customer point of view.

Basic Qualifications:
• Bachelor of Science or Master of Science in computing engineering or other relevant or equivalent education or experience
• 8+ years of experience in software programming and systems engineering.
• Very good knowledge and skills in Python
• Very good knowledge and skills in Docker and Kubernetes
• Very good knowledge in using Linux environments (system admin) and Bash scripting
• Very good knowledge and skills in AWS and cloud environments in general
• Fluency in English (our corporate language), spoken and written.

Preferred Qualifications:
• Good knowledge, skills and interest in DevSecOps
• Good knowledge, skills and interest in practicing product security by design
• A curious mind and a true continuous improvement mindset
• A team player with high integrity
• Experience in using and understanding agile methodology
• Relevant experience in Istio
• Relevant experience in Helm charts
• Relevant experience in Spring Cloud
• Good knowledge and skills in Java
• Good experience working with Go
• Relevant experience and interest in identity and authentication management.

This position is hybrid. This means that the selected candidate will be required to perform some work onsite 2-3 days a week. This is at the hiring team’s discretion and could potentially change in the future.

Relocation:
This position does not offer relocation. Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense.

Visa Sponsorship:
Employer will initiate the visa application; however, the successful candidate will cover the cost of visa.

Join us if you want to:

• Get professional skills development with our virtual learning tools and platforms (Digital Campus, LinkedIn Learning, Degreed, EdX, Enterprise Mentoring, and Communities of Excellence & Practice)

• Broaden your experience in international projects, technical workshops and hackathons

• Enjoy additional days off for Christmas break (December 24th-January 1st)

• Participate in employee recognition program (Boeing PridePoints)

• Have Private Medical Insurance (Skandia)

Please apply by sending your CV in English.

Export Control Requirements: Not an export control position

Equal Opportunity Employer:

We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not accept unlawful discrimination in our recruitment or employment practices on any grounds including but not limited to; race, color, ethnicity, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, physical or mental disability, genetic factors, military and veteran status, or other characteristics covered by applicable law.

We have teams in more than 65 countries, and each person plays a role in helping us become one of the world’s most innovative, diverse and inclusive companies. We are proud members of the Valuable 500 and welcome applications from candidates with disabilities. Applicants are encouraged to share with our recruitment team any accommodations required during the recruitment process. Accommodations may include but are not limited to: conducting interviews in accessible locations that accommodate mobility needs, encouraging candidates to bring and use any existing assistive technology such as screen readers and offering flexible interview formats such as virtual or phone interviews.

description:
Do you want to shape and maintain software development processes where compliance with standards and regulations is seamlessly integrated? Are you passionate about working hands-on with code to enhance tools, automation, and methodologies? Would you like to influence how we work with software development at Zenseact?

Apply today – no CV needed at the first stage! Just share your name, email, and phone number. We’ll take care of the rest later.

Insights from the Team

Our team is driven by the mission to create the safest possible software while delivering quality and safety-assured products. Our goal is to make it easier for developers to follow a seamless process, maintaining high-quality standards with robust tools and automation.

We’re forming a Software Process Core Team of four members and are looking for skilled developers to join us. Your focus will be on coding-level tasks and tool development, pioneering efforts to streamline compliance and enhance efficiency in software development.

Your Mission and Day-to-Day Tasks

You will be working hands-on with coding to improve our tools, automation, and methodologies. Typical tasks on a day-to-day basis include:

Maintain and improve the software development process.
Provide general support (e.g., answering questions in Slack).
Script and develop tools to support software development.
Build tools to measure process compliance and effectiveness.
Maintain and improve existing tools (e.g., FMEA, static architecture tools).
Create new tools to automate processes and simplify developers' daily work.
Keep self-audit tools and procedures up to date.
Deliver training sessions on the software development process.
Refine the methodology for the "Software Element Definition of Done."
Monitor and ensure process adherence across Zenseact teams.

What’s in It for You?

Directly influence Zenseact’s software development processes and tools.
Work on groundbreaking approaches to continuous compliance, a critical challenge in automotive software.
Be part of a forward-thinking company committed to safety, innovation, and inclusivity.
Collaborate with talented individuals from diverse backgrounds, fostering creativity and growth.
Enjoy a flexible work approach and genuine work-life balance.

Qualifications & Experience

Essential experience

Several years of experience in software development activities (e.g., requirement breakdown, architectural design, implementation, testing).
Expertise in safety and quality standards (e.g., ASPICE and ISO 26262).
Proficiency in Python and familiarity with Bazel.
Strong skills with Git and Gerrit.
Pedagogical abilities to train and support others effectively.

Nice to have, but absolutely not a must have!

A passion for developing tools and processes to simplify and improve software development workflows.

More about Zenseact

Our software makes a difference.

Using AI-based technology to create the ultimate driver support, we’re fighting to end car accidents and make roads safe for everyone. Every year, around 1.4 million people die in traffic while approximately 50 million people are injured. Many face lifelong challenges due to their injuries. We can do better.

One purpose, one product.

We’re a software company dedicated to revolutionizing car safety. By designing the complete software stack for autonomous driving and advanced driver-assistance systems, we’re pushing the boundaries of safety. Zenseact was founded by Volvo Cars, with teams based in Gothenburg and Lund Sweden, Munich in Germany and Shanghai, China. Our goal is to speed up the transition to safer automation through cutting-edge software and innovation.

Culture with people at heart

Achieving our mission to save lives and end traffic accidents requires us to venture into the unknown, pioneering new technology. While our expertise drives us, it’s our united culture that enables success. By fostering psychological safety, inclusion, and belonging, we ensure everyone can thrive.

Zenseact works proactively to create a culture of diversity and inclusion, valuing differences in gender, race, ethnicity, religion, disability, sexual orientation, and age. Diversity drives innovation, making it a cornerstone of our success.

Interviews are held continuously, so we highly recommend submitting your application as soon as possible!

description:
*We are looking for test engineers to our client in the automotive*

Join our dynamic team to shape the future of advanced driver assistance systems, infotainment, and connected experiences in the automotive industry. You will play a key role in developing and maintaining automation frameworks, improving test methodologies, and supporting the continuous integration infrastructure to ensure the highest quality standards in embedded systems.

*What you'll do*

As a Test Automation Engineer, you will take a key role in ensuring the quality and reliability of advanced automotive systems. Your responsibilities will span across developing and maintaining robust automation frameworks used to verify cutting-edge technologies, such as radar, lidar, and cameras. You will design and implement tools for data visualization, enabling clear and effective presentation of test results and metrics. Efficient database management will be a core aspect of your role, ensuring seamless storage and retrieval of critical test data.

You will also monitor and analyze automated tests, reporting defects and collaborating closely with developers to resolve issues. Supporting Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL) setups, you will fault-trace and enhance system reliability. Additionally, you will play a crucial role in improving rig operations and CI infrastructure, optimizing workflows to ensure stability and efficiency for development teams. In this role, you will collaborate across teams, sharing knowledge and providing training to stakeholders on test automation tools and processes.

*Who are you?*
* Strong Python programming skills, including experience with object-oriented design.
* Hands-on experience in HIL and SIL environments, and familiarity with simulation tools like dSPACE, CANoe, or CANalyzer.
* Proficiency in tools such as Grafana, PowerBI, Jenkins, or Zuul.
* Familiarity with Linux/QNX operating systems and shell scripting.
* Experience with test automation tools like Pytest, Robot Framework, or Selenium.
* Knowledge of continuous integration systems and cloud infrastructure (Azure or similar).
* Bachelor's degree in Engineering or equivalent experience.

*Ways to stand out from the crowd*
* Background in the automotive domain, particularly with advanced driver assistance systems (ADAS) or infotainment systems.
* Familiarity with UDS, XCP, HDF logging, and head-unit ECU development.
* Knowledge of Android Automotive OS and collaborations with partners like Google, Apple, and QNX.
* Experience with CI tools like Gerrit, Docker, Ansible, Terraform, and MongoDB.
* Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a proactive and self-driven mindset.

*Why join us*

Based in our vibrant Gothenburg office, this full-time role provides the chance to significantly influence the future of automotive technology. Our leadership extends beyond technical skills to fostering an environment where every team member can thrive. We support both professional and personal development, encouraging our team to explore new ideas and maintain a healthy work-life balance. As a member of our team, you'll spearhead not only technological innovation but also the creation of a culture that values diversity, learning, and collaboration. Join us in advancing automotive technology while cultivating a supportive and thriving team environment.

Jobbtyp: Heltid



Arbetstillstånd:
* Sverige (Obligatoriskt)


Arbetsort: Personligen

Supporting Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL) setups, you will fault-trace and enhance system reliability. Additionally, you will play a crucial role in improving rig operations and CI infrastructure, optimizing workflows to ensure stability and efficiency for development teams. In this role, you will collaborate across teams, sharing knowledge and providing training to stakeholders on test automation tools and processes.

Who are you?

  • Strong Python programming skills, including experience with object-oriented design.
  • Hands-on experience in HIL and SIL environments, and familiarity with simulation tools like dSPACE, CANoe, or CANalyzer.
  • Proficiency in tools such as Grafana, PowerBI, Jenkins, or Zuul.
  • Familiarity with Linux/QNX operating systems and shell scripting.
  • Experience with test automation tools like Pytest, Robot Framework, or Selenium.
  • Knowledge of continuous integration systems and cloud infrastructure (Azure or similar).
  • Bachelor's degree in Engineering or equivalent experience.

Ways to stand out from the crowd

  • Background in the automotive domain, particularly with advanced driver assistance systems (ADAS) or infotainment systems.
  • Familiarity with UDS, XCP, HDF logging, and head-unit ECU development.
  • Knowledge of Android Automotive OS and collaborations with partners like Google, Apple, and QNX.
  • Experience with CI tools like Gerrit, Docker, Ansible, Terraform, and MongoDB.
  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a proactive and self-driven mindset.

Why join us

Based in our vibrant Gothenburg office, this full-time role provides the chance to significantly influence the future of automotive technology. Our leadership extends beyond technical skills to fostering an environment where every team member can thrive. We support both professional and personal development, encouraging our team to explore new ideas and maintain a healthy work-life balance. As a member of our team, you'll spearhead not only technological innovation but also the creation of a culture that values diversity, learning, and collaboration. Join us in advancing automotive technology while cultivating a supportive and thriving team environment.

Jobbtyp: Heltid

Arbetstillstånd:

  • Sverige (Obligatoriskt)

Arbetsort: Personligen

description:
We are looking for a senior Business Intelligence expert to contribute to our client’s significant effort of migrating an extensive data warehouse, with its ETL process, data, and reporting solutions to an AWS cloud environment.
The solution to be migrated houses historic data of financial trades from decades back.

Mandatory Requirements

* Expertise in Power BI, gathering requirements, designing and developing middle layers (logical layer, semantic layer)

* Expertise in designing and implementing dashboards and reports in Power BI

* Experience working with and designing solutions for large data volumes

* Expertise in how to work in and govern production environments, and ensuring documentation (reports, dashboards) throughout the product lifecycle

* Expertise in data warehousing (Dimensional data modeling ETL processes) in a PostgreSQL environment

* Fluent English

* AWS knowledge is a merit

Roles and Responsibilities

• Contribute to the migration of a BI environment from a traditional on-prem to an AWS cloud platform, applying best practices

• Produce requirements and also design and implement the middle layer (logical layer, semantic layer) in a 3-layer BI implementation

• Contribute to, and also coordinate the migration work of extensive dashboards and reports to use the build middle-layer data sets

• Ensuring business documentation of requirements and solutions

• Contributing to and coordinating with SMEs regarding quality assurance, testing and reconciliation

• Identify opportunities to streamline, simplify or reduce the existing scope of reports and solutions

• Support analysts and other data consumers in the transition to the new business intelligence tool, including support with data queries, troubleshooting and training

The scope of the full migration project:

• ETL solutions in SQL Server (stored procedures, SSIS) and the occasional command, R or Python scripts

• SQL Server data warehouse, with several databases and data models, including the historic data

• QlikView apps and their dashboards and their server-side views

• A SAP Business Objects universe and an extensive set of reports used by several business stakeholders

We expect you to have:

• A degree in a relevant field

• Many years of relevant working experience

• Expertise in Power BI and preferably other BI tools, doing development work both back-end and front-end

• Expertise in data warehousing (normalized data models, slowly changing dimensions, ETL processes etc.) in a PostgreSQL environment

• Expertise in how to work in and govern production environments, and ensuring documentation throughout the product lifecycle

• Experience working with and designing solutions for large data volumes – millions or 100x observations daily

• Fluent English language skills

It would be great if you also possess:

• Experience migrating data solutions into AWS

• Mastery of AWS and Redshift

• Experience with cloud service providers and relevant microservices

• Experience with programming languages R and Python, and scripting languages PowerShell and Visual Basic

• Experience from business intelligence tools SAP Business Objects and QlikView

• Familiarity with trading data, trades and quotes

• A good understanding of statistical analysis and advanced analytics

In order to succeed in this role, we believe that you are structured, analytical, and thorough in your work in order to handle a migration of an extensive and complex solution at the end of its lifecycle.

ABOUT MBE

ADVANCED TECHNOLOGY AND MANAGEMENT

MBE have solid experience of sustainable product development in Automotive and Clean Energy Tech industry in combination with advanced AI for electrical grid (similar to stock market). After several awards for technical expertise from European Council, Swedish Energy Agency and Västra Götalandsregionen as well as growth and leadership such as DI Gazelle with successful international business we feel confident in our progress and are welcoming additional exeperts to the journey.

We created and developed our distinguished leadership model together with professors at IHM Personal Leadership program and Stephen R Covey’s methodology. You will recognize many similarities in Simon Sinek’s visions. The model is continuously sharpened since 2001.

VERSATILE & INCLUSIVE TEAM

We are happy to see applications from creative, curious and senior developers to join our expert team towards advanced technology clients within Automotive and Circular Energy. We are extra happy to see applications from FEMALE applicants.

We engage top engineers. Experienced experts as well as distinguished Newly graduated engineers with personal values for Sustainable Engineering, IT and Embedded solutions, caring for a well balanced life with family & fun together with YOUR best career development!

3D CAREER PLAN

Successful companies build a well-planned business plan. MBE builds successful people through their individual “Personal Business Plan”! Since we have a wide palette of recognized international clients and assignments, there’s always a matching assignment connecting to YOUR career plan.

Through the MBE’s solid leadership model, our employees develop their career in 3D! Through long-term planning, between the 3D parts Work, Health and Social life, together with challenging assignments, important contacts and supplementary courses to become the best they can be… with their own individual prerequisites!

APPLY, DEVELOP AND CREATE YOUR FUTURE!

We hope you find this attempting to be a part of! Join us on the travel to YOUR best future! Apply, Develop and Create Your Future! Now!

Send your application as soon as possible to jobb@mutualbenefits.se

description:
About this role

We are now looking for an expert, preferably with a PhD, in computer vision, image analysis, machine learning or other areas related to computer vision, as well as talented engineers with extensive industrial experience from these fields.

You will be part of cutting-edge computer vision projects as we continue our journey to develop our video analytics solutions. We also actively participate as consultants in select projects in other industries than our own to continuously challenge ourselves. We expect you to participate in the daily work of our systems design and development of algorithms as well as being part of our external consultancy projects from time to time.

What we offer

Our R&D department consists of tight agile teams, where most people contribute to several aspects of the system. We strongly believe in, and our company culture is based on, freedom and responsibility. For us, that means you will be given extensive freedom to make strategic technical decisions while meeting our high standards and making decisions in a responsible way. You will be located at our headquarters in buzzing Lindholmen, Gothenburg, where we are a welcoming team with a lot of positive energy and a strong sense of community.

We care for each other and strive to recruit the most skilled and innovative individuals as we believe that every employee truly drives Irisity to success. We promise that you will get your fair share of technical challenges within the field of computer vision and machine learning and a stimulating environment to grow your skill set.

Who we think you are

To be successful in this role, we expect you to have extensive programming experience, such that you can autonomously develop and understand complex source code and algorithms. A thorough understanding of organizational aspects of software development and collaborating efficiently within a development team are indispensable skills for this role. As personal qualities, we value creativity and assertiveness, along with a friendly and collaborative tone and open-mindedness.

Requirements

Proven ability to deliver high-quality results from your previous work and/or state-of-the-art scientific output
Ph.D. or M.Sc. related to the fields of computer vision, machine learning or related areas
Minimum 5 years of programming experience (in Python or C++)
Minimum 4 years of computer vision algorithm development including deep learning
A strong desire to collaborate with others and to contribute to team success
Proficiency in English. Swedish is a plus but not a requirement.

Expertise in any of the following areas is advantageous

Visual object tracking, camera geometry, and calibration
Training machine learning models at scale, including managing large datasets and implementing data pipelines
Optimizing models for inference
Linux environments, containerization (e.g., Docker), and build tools (e.g., CMake, CircleCI)

About Irisity

At Irisity, we develop video analytics software for the security industry with great respect for personal integrity and privacy, focusing on detecting suspicious activity rather than exposing personal identity. Our system excels at the automatic detection of unwanted activity, such as intruders at construction sites at night, or people climbing roofs or breaking windows. We focus on detecting and preventing criminal activity without registering the identity of regular citizens. At sensitive installations such as schools, our system anonymizes all individuals to hide their identity, to make sure that the invasion of privacy is kept at a zero level. This way, our system can detect what happens and alert, leading to reduced crime rates and increased safety without any negative effects on personal privacy.

Irisity AB (publ) is a public company listed at OMX Nasdaq First North, with offices in Sweden, Israel, Hungary, USA, Singapore, the UAE and Brazil. We currently employ a staff of 90+ people within development, sales, support and finance. Our R&D department consists of a computer vision / machine learning team and an excellent group of system architects, designers and software developers. Our software is packaged into a complete cloud-based SaaS platform marketed towards large global customers and with thousands of cameras connected.

We are looking forward to receiving your application. We highly encourage you to apply even if you don’t fulfill all the listed requirements but think you would fit into the role. As a global company, we value diverse, inclusive teams that can contribute to our team success through their unique perspectives, experiences and backgrounds. Selection and interviews will be performed continuously until the role is filled.

Read more at www.irisity.com

description:
About Embedl

Embedl is a fast-growing technology start-up based in Gothenburg, Sweden. With a team of over 20 dedicated professionals, we are on a mission to make AI affordable and efficient in embedded systems. Our development team is headquartered in Gothenburg, and our innovative solutions serve customers all over the world. We maintain close connections with academic research institutions, industry leaders, and the innovation ecosystem, supported by strong relationships with venture capital partners.

The Role

We are seeking a talented Deep Learning Engineer to join our team in developing our flagship product, the Embedl SDK—a Python library that empowers businesses to create efficient AI models, optimized for embedded hardware.

Responsibilities

Implementing features and functions in Embedl’s software products to enhance performance and user experience.
Benchmarking optimization algorithms by training models and deploying them to hardware.
Improving hardware support by integrating AI tools from industry leaders such as Nvidia, Intel, Xilinx, ARM, Qualcomm, STMicroelectronics, Ambarella, Texas Instruments, and NXP.

Who You Are

You are a curious and hands-on developer with excellent problem-solving skills, ready to help us deliver a modern and high-quality software product. You are self-driven, communicative, and thrive when given high-level responsibilities and complex problems to solve. As a team player, you are eager to learn from others and contribute to a positive working environment.

Qualifications

Must-Have

Academic degree in Computer Science, Physics, Electrical Engineering, or equivalent skills achieved through experience.
Excellent coding skills in Python.
Experience developing deep learning models using PyTorch, Jax, Keras and/or TensorFlow.
Experience with libraries for scientific computing, such as Numpy, Scipy and Matplotlib.
2-5 years of industry experience in software development, preferably in sectors like automotive or telecom where code quality is paramount.

Nice-to-Have

Familiarity with developing AI models for embedded hardware.
Experience with C, C++, CUDA.
FPGA or embedded programming.
Knowledge of data visualization tools.
Experience working in a Linux environment.
Experience with Git, Docker, and Agile methodologies.

What We Offer

Collaborative Culture: Join a high-performance team that values teamwork, knowledge sharing, and a positive working environment.

Professional Growth: Opportunities for continuous learning, mentorship, and career advancement.

Benefits: Health and wellness allowance (friskvårdsbidrag) of 5000 SEK and private health insurance.

Application Process

The selection and interview process is ongoing, so please send your application in English as soon as possible. For any questions or clarifications, reach out to Anna-Maria Sjölund at anna.maria@embedl.com.

You are welcome at Embedl for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what your favorite IDE is.

Join us at Embedl and be a part of shaping the future of efficient AI!

description:
Do you want to be part of shaping the future of ticketing and event tech? At Tickster, we’re all about creating experiences and memories that last a lifetime – for millions of people, every year. Now, we’re looking for talented Computer Science and Software Engineering students ready to jump into an exciting thesis project with us.

About Tickster

Tickster has grown into Scandinavia's largest platform for ticket sales and event management, with over 5,500 organizers who trust us to handle everything from ticket sales to event logistics. Today, we’re selling a ticket every 3rd second!

Our platform goes beyond tickets – from restaurant and bar sales to mobile ordering, our system helps clients manage their events with ease. With offices in Arvika and Gothenburg, Oslo (NO) and Roskilde (DK), a culture of collaboration, and a passion for growth, we’re here to keep expanding across Scandinavia and Europe .

What We Offer

A meaningful thesis project where you’ll apply your skills in real-world scenarios, gaining invaluable experience in tech and event management.
Mentorship and guidance from experienced developers and product teams to support your project goals.
Collaboration with an agile team working on the forefront of product and tech development.
Opportunities to make an impact and implement your ideas in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.

Possible Project Areas, here are some ideas...

Machine Learning Approaches for Detecting and Preventing Ticket Scalping and Bot Activity
Real-Time Purchase Pattern Analysis for Customized Sales and Promotion
Developing AI-Powered Self-Service Tools for Event Organizer Support System
Optimizing High-Performance Seat Search Algorithms in Event Management Systems
Developing Accessible Webshop Interfaces
Cache Invalidation Strategies for Data Consistency in Distributed Systems
AI-Driven Real-Time Anomaly Detection in High-Volume Log Streams
Robust Algorithms for Data Synchronization in Distributed Systems
Implementing and Evaluating Dynamic Pricing Strategies for Ticket Sales with Consumer Perception in Mind.

Do you have another project idea in mind? We are happy to discuss your proposal.

Qualifications

Current or recent studies in Computer Science and Engineering (D), Software Engineering (IT), or related fields with expected graduation during Spring 2026 (already appointed for 2025)
Interest in the tech industry and a passion for developing innovative solutions.
Strong programming skills, preferably in languages relevant for web development or backend (e.g., C#, JavaScript, Python, Java).

Interested?
Please send a short statement about your interest, along with your CV and any initial thoughts on your thesis project.

Contact us:
We accept expressions of interest on a rolling basis and look forward to hearing from you!

description:
Does this sound like you?

Skilled Frontend Developer: You've spent recent years mastering web technologies like React, Vue.js, or Next.js.
Pragmatic Backend Developer: You’ve dipped your toes into Node.js and know your way around deploying and maintaining backend services on platforms like AWS, Google Cloud, Firebase, Supabase, or Vercel.
Multilingual: You are fluent in TypeScript, JavaScript and have a good understanding of other programming languages as well.
Mobile Curious: You been working with mobile development before, either native iOS or Android or even cross-platform using React Native or Flutter.
If your answer is 4x YES, you should definitely reach out to us!

Future Memories is deeply engaged in the exciting world of AI. We are running AI-driven services in production, continuously improving them on a daily basis.
Hands-on experience with latest AI models, RAG, MLOps together with a strong interest in rapid prototyping in either TypeScript or Python is a big plus!

Join our team of seasoned full stack and data engineers and craft exceptional experiences in tight collaboration with our world-class, award-winning design team.

Be part of success stories like SGS, Weekly Revolt, STC, or our very own venture inblick.ai.

Future Memories is deeply engaged in the exciting world of AI. We are running AI-driven services in production, continuously improving them on a daily basis.
Hands-on experience with latest AI models, RAG, MLOps together with a strong interest in rapid prototyping in either TypeScript or Python is a big plus!

Join our team of seasoned full stack and data engineers and craft exceptional experiences in tight collaboration with our world-class, award-winning design team.

Be part of success stories like SGS, Weekly Revolt, STC, or our very own venture inblick.ai.

description:
Ansök här
AI Expert at Twinfinity Gothenburg

Are you looking for a job where you can really make a difference? Do you want to create new ways of creating value within real estate? Are you up for a challenge?

As an AI Expert at Twinfinity you are a member of a passionate, skilled, cross-functional team that manages itself and is responsible for developing our ecosystem of digital twin apps. You will be part of an industry evolution, grow as a developer and human, and make life easier for people in the huge construction industry.

How we work

We are an agile organisation that cares about its people and is serious about work and play. Work-life balance is essential to us! We offer a competitive salary, encourage learning, health and have good benefits.

We pride ourselves on our openness, flexible work schedules, exploration days, expansive industry knowledge and respect for individual lifestyles.

On a typical day you

Are an active part of a cross-functional team, collaborating daily with all parts of the organisation. We work together!
Work at the office at least two days per week and remotely when you need to
Share what you know and learn what you don’t
Are proactive and get things done (We don’t micromanage)
Fail fast and learn from the experience
Have fun with your colleagues!

As an AI Expert at Twinfinity you will be

Creating insights from a vast amount of data
Coming up with new ideas for value creating applications that we can add to our range of applications
Helping the organisation use AI for improved operations and increased efficiency

Examples of valuable skills

Deep learning frameworks (e.g. TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch)
Neural networks, designing and training different types of networks (e.g. CNN, RNN, GAN)
Programming languages (Python / R / C++)
Supervised learning algorithms using regression, classification, and decision trees (e.g. SVM, random forest)
Unsupervised learning algorithms using clustering (e.g. K-Means, DBSCAN) or dimensionality reduction (e.g. PCA)
Large language models (LLM)
Natural language processing (NLP) with skills in text processing, sentiment analysis, language models, and transformer-based models (e.g. BERT, GPT)
Computer vision using object detection, image classification, segmentation using CNN
Data science and statistics
Big data and databases (especially MSSQL and PostgreSQL)
Git
Spoken and written English

If you are experienced in any of these areas, great!

Are you the person we are looking for?

We believe that you have worked in the field of AI/ML for at least a few years and as a general developer for a few more years. You have personal experience in using AI in a business environment with real world scenarios and know how to make sense of and manage training data.

You need to be a doer. There are many other people that can help you get access to data, but you need to be able to take it from there. Being a “manager of one” you define and carry out the tasks required to take an idea to a finished proof-of-concept and then work with our teams to take it to a finished product.

This is Twinfinity

Twinfinity is a subsidiary of Sweco. We were founded in 2022 as a product company with a vision of revolutionising the real estate industry through innovative solutions within digital twins. Through our platform and individual applications, we provide insights and tools for property owner, helping them to make the right decisions and, at the same time, minimise the negative impact on our planet.

We are a quickly growing SaaS company with high ambitions where what is possible is mostly limited by our imaginations. We have an entrepreneurial culture and consists of 30+ employees.

The geographical placement of this role is Gothenburg.

We’d love to hear from you!

The application process

Please observe that we review applications continuously and the position may be filled before the application deadline. Applications received during the holiday season will be reviewed when we are back from vacations.

Contact us!

If you have questions or want to hear more about what it is like being part of our crew, don’t hesitate to contact;
Martin Bergek, Product and Technology Manager Twinfinity
martin.bergek@twinfinity.com
 +46 733 017470.

We are handling the recruitment ourselves and kindly ask all recruitment and consulting firms to not contact us in this matter, thanks!

description:
Are you an Android development expert with a passion for creating innovative applications? Do you thrive in dynamic environments and enjoy tackling complex challenges? SiNIX invites you to join our mission to revolutionize technology solutions across diverse industries.

Who We're Looking For
We seek Android developers who are not just experienced but passionate about making a tangible impact. You should have:

An MSc in system development or equivalent.
Knowledge of the Android platform (Android Automotive and AOSP).
At least 5 years of experience in system development with Java and/or C++ in a Linux environment.
Experience working in agile environments and knowledge of CI/CD.
Proficiency with tools like GIT, Jira, Confluence, and Python.

At SiNIX, you'll dive into projects spanning autonomous vehicles (ADAS), Active Safety, IoT, Application development, Cyber security, 5G and MedTech. We embrace project-based assignments, full-team deliveries, and flexible staffing, ensuring both variety and depth in your work.

Our Offer
With us, you set your own salary, and the majority of the surplus from your assignment goes to your plan for bonuses, education, insurance, vacation days, parental leave, pension, stock savings, etc. This flexible model has proven to be suitable for developers who have experienced conventional compensation models but desire more freedom.

About SiNIX
As a leader in software consultancy, SiNIX Application thrives at the intersection of cloud computing and on-premise solutions. Our expertise spans across custom software development, full-stack cloud solutions, security enhancements, and the innovative realms of Kubernetes and IoT. We cherish the value each colleague brings to our team, fostering an environment where sharing skills and memorable experiences is part of our daily routine.

At SiNIX, we prioritize the value of our colleagues by creating memorable experiences and sharing skills. We empower our employees with choices in training, vacation time, and flexible salaries, fostering a supportive and thriving work environment. We aim to inspire ongoing growth and development, making success a shared journey.

Apply now
...and explore how your expertise can contribute to our shared success and innovation.
